# Dream Image Generator - Project Structure

This is a Next.js 14 TypeScript project for AI image generation using Google's Gemini API.

## Key Directories
- `app/` - Next.js App Router pages and API routes
- `components/` - Reusable React components
- `lib/` - Utility libraries and configurations
- `utils/` - Utility functions and external service integrations
- `memory-bank/` - Project documentation and context

## Important Files
- [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Main homepage
- [app/api/generate/route.ts](mdc:app/api/generate/route.ts) - Image generation API endpoint
- [components/ImageUploader.tsx](mdc:components/ImageUploader.tsx) - Main image upload component
- [components/Header.tsx](mdc:components/Header.tsx) - Navigation header
- [lib/presets.ts](mdc:lib/presets.ts) - Image generation presets
- [utils/supabase/server.ts](mdc:app/utils/supabase/server.ts) - Supabase server client

## Path Aliases
- Use `@/` prefix for imports from project root
- Example: `import { createClient } from '@/utils/supabase/server'`